# Design And Content Standards

- Prefer existing shadcn/Base UI components in `src/components/ui`, foundation components in `src/components/foundations`, and nearby feature components before creating new primitives.
- Use semantic design tokens such as `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-background`, `bg-surface`, `bg-muted`, and `border-border`. Avoid raw Tailwind palette classes like `blue-500`, `slate-200`, or `gray-900`.
- Avoid `mb-*` for page-level vertical spacing. Prefer `mt-*`, `gap-*`, or `space-y-*`.
- Use `Text.astro` for page-level titles and descriptions in shared layouts.
- Keep docs, legal, and support copy in content collections under `src/content/*`; render them through Astro pages/layouts instead of hardcoding copy in route files.
- Avoid unrelated redesigns, formatting sweeps, or refactors when making focused content or UI changes.
